The paper proposes a new loss function for few-shot classification, which is a problem commonly studied in the machine learning community. The paper also conducts experiments on image datasets, indicating that the paper may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the model capacity for few-shot classification tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of pre-trained models, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper proposes a new loss function, which may also be of interest to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
